The paper presents a method for program synthesis using refinement types, which are a type-based approach to specifying program behavior. This makes it most likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. However, the paper also discusses the decidability and verification aspects of refinement types, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the usability and scalability of the proposed method, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the reduction in the size of the search space, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
